Chicago Bulls point guard Derrick Rose wore a black 'I Can't Breathe' T-shirt during warm-up before playing the Golden State Warriors on Saturday night.

The shirt refers to a New York man who died in July after a police officer placed him in a chokehold when he was being arrested for selling loose, untaxed cigarettes.

A grand jury decided it would not indict the officer in Eric Garner's death. 

